{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01F7HAEQWEu5vi3VuUxsdJmX","type":"tool_result","content":"A node failed to rejoin the cluster after a restart.\n\nRestore full membership while keeping the cluster healthy.\n\nConstraints:\n- Do not install operators or CRDs.\n- Keep the cluster healthy.\n\nVerification:\n1. Cluster health is yellow/green.\n2. All nodes appear in /_cat/nodes.\n3. app-data remains readable.===PRECOND===\n[precondition:es_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'es_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n5\n\n[precondition:seed_hosts_index_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'seed_hosts_index_fixture':probe] $ /bin/sh -c 'pw=$(kubectl -n elasticsearch get secret elastic-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null); A=\"\"; [ -n \"$pw\" ] && A=\"-u elastic:$pw\"; kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A --max-time 5 \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/app-data/_count\" 2>/dev/null | grep -q \"\\\"count\\\"\"'\n\n[precondition:seed_hosts_index_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'seed_hosts_index_fixture':apply] $ /bin/sh -c 'pw=$(kubectl -n elasticsearch get secret elastic-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null); A=\"\"; [ -n \"$pw\" ] && A=\"-u elastic:$pw\"; kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A -XPUT \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/app-data\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d \"{\\\"settings\\\":{\\\"number_of_shards\\\":1,\\\"number_of_replicas\\\":1}}\" >/dev/null 2>&1; kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A -XPOST \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/app-data/_doc\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d \"{\\\"msg\\\":\\\"seed\\\"}\" >/dev/null 2>&1; true'\n\n[precondition:seed_hosts_index_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'seed_hosts_index_fixture':verify] $ /bin/sh -c 'pw=$(kubectl -n elasticsearch get secret elastic-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.